title: Actress Maureen O'Hara dies
text:
Actress Maureen O'Hara dies Movie legend was 95 Tweet Frazer Harrison/Getty Images 
Maureen O'Hara, the red-headed actress who appeared in Hollywood classics such as "How Green Was My Valley," "The Quiet Man" and holiday staple "Miracle on 34th Street" has died. Related Content By Frank Pallotta 
She was 95. 
O'Hara's manager said she died in her sleep at her home in Boise, Idaho, ABC News reports. 
Born in Ranelagh, Dublin, Ireland, in 1920, the Abbey Theatre-trained O'Hara became a naturalized U.S. citizen in 1946 and held dual Irish-U.S. citizenship, the Irish Times reports. 
O'Hara worked with actors John Wayne, Tyrone Power, James Stewart, Henry Fonda and Anthony Quinn, Bloomberg reports, and worked with directors Alfred Hitchcock, Carol Reed, Henry Hathaway and Jean Renoir, among others. 
In 2014, the Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences awarded her the Honorary Oscar. Distributed by LAKANA. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed.
